Mid-infrared and fluorescence spectra of sample were collected by a spectrum 65 FT-IR spectrometer (Perkin Elmer, United States) and a FP-6500 spectrofluorometer (Jasco, Japan), respectively. The structure and crystalline phase of the sample was characterized by an Axs-D8 Advance powder X-ray diffractometer (XRD) (Bruker, Germany) using Cu-kα radiation (λ= 1.54178
A °
). The 2θ range was formed 4 to 80° with scanning steps of 2θ = 4°min-1 . A flame atomic absorption (FAA) spectrometer (model 1100 B, Perkin Elmer, United States) was used to determine the concentration of metal ions.
